Early stopping parameter for CLIP model;: Early stopping parameter for CLIP model; 1 is stop at last layer as usual, 2 is stop at penultimate layer, etc.
5. ｢すべての変更を保存｣ ボタンが押されるまで、変更はテキスト ファイルに適: 5. ｢すべての変更を保存｣ ボタンが押されるまで、変更はテキスト ファイルに適用されません。
選択した画像に変更を適用: 選択した画像に変更を適用
Prompt (press Ctrl+Enter or Alt+Enter to: プロンプト (Ctrl+Enter か Alt+Enter を押して生成)
Negative prompt (press Ctrl+Enter or Alt: ネガティブプロンプト (Ctrl+Enter か Alt+Enter を押して生成)
Read generation parameters from prompt o: Read generation parameters from prompt or last generation if prompt is empty into user interface.
Apply selected styles to current prompt: Apply selected styles to current prompt
Add a random artist to the prompt.
Stop processing current image and contin: Stop processing current image and continue processing.
Stop processing images and return any re: Stop processing images and return any results accumulated so far.
Style to apply; styles have components f: Style to apply; styles have components for both positive and negative prompts and apply to both
Which algorithm to use to produce the im: Which algorithm to use to produce the image
Euler Ancestral - very creative, each ca: Euler Ancestral - very creative, each can get a completely different picture depending on step count, setting steps higher than 30-40 does not help
How many times to improve the generated: How many times to improve the generated image iteratively; higher values take longer; very low values can produce bad results
How many batches of images to create: How many batches of images to create
How many image to create in a single bat: How many image to create in a single batch
Classifier Free Guidance Scale - how str: Classifier Free Guidance Scale - how strongly the image should conform to prompt - lower values produce more creative results
A value that determines the output of ra: A value that determines the output of random number generator - if you create an image with same parameters and seed as another image, you'll get the same result
Set seed to -1, which will cause a new r: Set seed to -1, which will cause a new random number to be used every time
Reuse seed from last generation, mostly: Reuse seed from last generation, mostly useful if it was randomed
Seed of a different picture to be mixed: Seed of a different picture to be mixed into the generation.
How strong of a variation to produce. At: How strong of a variation to produce. At 0, there will be no effect. At 1, you will get the complete picture with variation seed (except for ancestral samplers, where you will just get something).
Make an attempt to produce a picture sim: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution
Produce an image that can be tiled.
Use a two step process to partially crea: Use a two step process to partially create an image at smaller resolution, upscale, and then improve details in it without changing composition
Number of sampling steps for upscaled pi: Number of sampling steps for upscaled picture. If 0, uses same as for original.
Determines how little respect the algori: Determines how little respect the algorithm should have for image's content. At 0, nothing will change, and at 1 you'll get an unrelated image. With values below 1.0, processing will take less steps than the Sampling Steps slider specifies.
Adjusts the size of the image by multipl: Adjusts the size of the image by multiplying the original width and height by the selected value. Ignored if either Resize width to or Resize height to are non-zero.
Resizes image to this width. If 0, width: Resizes image to this width. If 0, width is inferred from either of two nearby sliders.
Resizes image to this height. If 0, heig: Resizes image to this height. If 0, height is inferred from either of two nearby sliders.
Separate values for X axis using commas.
Separate values for Y axis using commas.
Write image to a directory (default - lo: Write image to a directory (default - log/images) and generation parameters into csv file.
How much to blur the mask before process: How much to blur the mask before processing, in pixels.
What to put inside the masked area befor: What to put inside the masked area before processing it with Stable Diffusion.
fill it with colors of the image: fill it with colors of the image
fill it with latent space noise: fill it with latent space noise
fill it with latent space zeroes: fill it with latent space zeroes
Resize image to target resolution. Unles: Resize image to target resolution. Unless height and width match, you will get incorrect aspect ratio.
Resize the image so that entirety of tar: Resize the image so that entirety of target resolution is filled with the image. Crop parts that stick out.
Resize the image so that entirety of ima: Resize the image so that entirety of image is inside target resolution. Fill empty space with image's colors.
How many times to repeat processing an i: How many times to repeat processing an image and using it as input for the next iteration
In loopback mode, on each loop the denoi: In loopback mode, on each loop the denoising strength is multiplied by this value. <1 means decreasing variety so your sequence will converge on a fixed picture. >1 means increasing variety so your sequence will become more and more chaotic.
For SD upscale, how much overlap in pixe: For SD upscale, how much overlap in pixels should there be between tiles. Tiles overlap so that when they are merged back into one picture, there is no clearly visible seam.
A directory on the same machine where th: サーバーが稼働しているのと同じマシンにあるフォルダ
Leave blank to save images to the defaul: 空欄でデフォルトの場所へ画像を保存
1st and last digit must be 1. ex:'1, 2,: 最初と最後の数字は1でなければなりません。 例:'1, 2, 1'
1st and last digit must be 0 and values: 1st and last digit must be 0 and values should be between 0 and 1. ex:'0, 0.01, 0'
Path to directory with input images: 入力ファイルのあるフォルダの場所
Path to directory where to write outputs: 出力を書き込むフォルダの場所
List of tags, delimited by spaces: List of tags, delimited by spaces
Negative prompt to send with along with: Negative prompt to send with along with each prompt
Enter embedding name (only first token i: Enter embedding name (only first token is processed), or embedding ID as #nnnnn
Enter a short prompt (loaded embeddings: Enter a short prompt (loaded embeddings or modifiers are not supported)
Enter name of embedding to mix: Enter name of embedding to mix
